=head1 DESCRIPTION

Information about the post-contact summary for a real-time contact
segment.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Content => Str

The content of the summary.


=head2 FailureCode => Str

If the summary failed to be generated, one of the following failure
codes occurs:

=over

=item *

C<QUOTA_EXCEEDED>: The number of concurrent analytics jobs reached your
service quota.

=item *

C<INSUFFICIENT_CONVERSATION_CONTENT>: The conversation needs to have at
least one turn from both the participants in order to generate the
summary.

=item *

C<FAILED_SAFETY_GUIDELINES>: The generated summary cannot be provided
because it failed to meet system safety guidelines.

=item *

C<INVALID_ANALYSIS_CONFIGURATION>: This code occurs when, for example,
you're using a language
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/connect/latest/adminguide/supported-languages.html#supported-languages-contact-lens)
that isn't supported by generative AI-powered post-contact summaries.

=item *

C<INTERNAL_ERROR>: Internal system error.

=back



=head2 B<REQUIRED> Status => Str

Whether the summary was successfully COMPLETED or FAILED to be
generated.



